radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is fluid filled, measuring up to 8 mm in diameter, with hyperemia of the mucosa. There is trace mesenteric fat stranding surrounding it. There are prominent mesenteric lymph nodes near the cecum which are likely reactive. The lower chest, liver, gallbladder, biliary tree, spleen, adrenal glands, pancreas, kidneys, stomach, small bowel, large bowel, urinary bladder, prostate, and rectum appear normal. No fluid collection, pneumoperitoneum, or free fluid in the abdomen. No destructive osseous lesions concerning for malignancy or infection.
